ost <a rel="nofollow" href="http://connections-pro.com/2016/08/12/quicktip-add-custom-phone-types/">QuickTip: Add Custom Phone Types</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Steven Zahm";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3080:"<p>In this QuickTip I’ll walk through how to add custom phone types to the phone fieldset. Before moving on, the first thing you should do is install the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/code-snippets/">Code Snippets plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>To add new phone types you need to hook into <code>cn_phone_options</code> filter. This filter supplies an array containing the core phone types. The array key is the phone type ID and the array value is the phone label.</p>\n<p>The phone key ID needs to be in all lowercase using underscores in places of spaces and the phone label can be any text that you wish.</p>\n<p>The following example code adds two new phone types named &#8220;Shipping&#8221; and &#8220;Receiving&#8221;.</p>\n\n<div class="wp_syntax"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre class="php" style="font-family:monospace;"><span style="color: #000000; font-weight: bold;">function</span> cn_my_new_phone_types<span style="color: #009900;">&#40;</span> <span style="color: #000088;">$options</span> <span style="color: #009900;">&#41;</span> <span style="color: #009900;">&#123;</span>\n&nbsp;\n    <span style="color: #000088;">$options</span><span style="color: #009900;">&#91;</span><span style="color: #0000ff;">''shipping''</span><span style="color: #009900;">&#93;</span>  <span style="color: #339933;">=</span> <span style="color: #0000ff;">''Shipping''</span><span style="color: #339933;">;</span>\n    <span style="color: #000088;">$options</span><span style="color: #009900;">&#91;</span><span style="color: #0000ff;">''receiving''</span><span style="color: #009900;">&#93;</span> <span style="color: #339933;">=</span> <span style="color: #0000ff;">''Receiving''</span><span style="color: #339933;">;</span>\n&nbsp;\n    <span style="color: #b1b100;">return</span> <span style="color: #000088;">$options</span><span style="color: #339933;">;</span>\n<span style="color: #009900;">&#125;</span>\n&nbsp;\nadd_filter<span style="color: #009900;">&#40;</span> <span style="color: #0000ff;">''cn_phone_options''</span><span style="color: #339933;">,</span> <span style="color: #0000ff;">''cn_my_new_phone_types''</span> <span style="color: #009900;">&#41;</span><span style="color: #339933;">;</span></pre></td></tr></table></div>\n\n<p>To see this example code in action, copy/paste it as a new code snippet using the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/code-snippets/">Code Snippets plugin</a>. <em><strong>Save and Activate</strong></em> the new code snippet with &#8220;Run snippet everywhere&#8221; option selected.</p>\n<p>Now, when you add a new entry, you will see the new phone types &#8220;Shipping&#8221; and &#8220;Receiving&#8221; as options.</p>\n<p>Using this method you can add as many phone types as you need.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://connections-pro.com/2016/08/12/quicktip-add-custom-phone-types/">QuickTip: Add Custom Phone Types</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/6vvE1k1I-ng" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://connections-pro.com/2016/08/12/quicktip-add-custom-phone-types/feed/";s:7:"attr